<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-156-055 </DOCNO><DOCID>10 723 961</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic News  May 13 1991 v37 n1860 p14(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>NSC to buy Vitalink for $146 million. (Network Systems Corp. buysVitalink Communications Corp.)andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>Collier, Andrew.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Network Systems Corp (NSC) will acquire Vitalink CommunicationsCorp for $146 million in a move expected to improve bothVitalink's product development and NSC's router business andmarketing efforts.andP;  NSC will give its router business to Vitalinkto manage while focusing on its core business of high-end computercommunications products.andP;  The companies will operate separatelyfor now.andP;  In FY 1990, NSC had earnings of $22 million on sales of$164 million; Vitalink earned $8.9 million on sales of $67million.andP;  Some analysts believe that Vitalink shareholders did notreceive enough remuneration in the acquisition: Vitalink has $100million in cash on its balance sheet, which effectively reducesthe price NSC paid.andP;  NSC's timing is particularly good because thecompany can use Vitalink's strong marketing abilities to marketits relatively new local area network internetworking products.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Network Systems Corp. (Acquisitions, mergers, divestments)Vitalink Communications Corp. (Acquisitions, mergers,divestments).andO;Ticker:    VITA; NSCO.andO;Topic:     AcquisitionData CommunicationsRouters (Connector)Communications Equipment.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>